ricker
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a pole or spar cut from a long, slender tree-trunk; the trunk of such a tree; (occas ?) such a tree
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ?d. Ed Fairburn Makaratanga 29 [cut] long, thin `Rickers' and made them into ladders. (Auckland bushmen's and forestry general) (occas. rika) a kauri sapling; a kauri-tree in the pole stage
